WEBVTT

00:18.512 --> 00:20.210
I have in my hands
the heart of a witch!

00:20.253 --> 00:21.863
[Cheering]

00:21.907 --> 00:23.778
There's a whole group of them
posting about witches.

00:23.822 --> 00:25.389
Rowan: Leave me alone.

00:25.432 --> 00:26.825
Tell him what you want.
He's part of you.

00:26.868 --> 00:28.870
I want him gone.Ciprien: If I can understand

00:28.914 --> 00:31.134
how the connection between
Lasher and the family began,

00:31.177 --> 00:33.049
then I have a better
chance of ending it.

00:33.092 --> 00:36.008
[Chanting]

00:36.052 --> 00:38.402
All of this to be rid of me?Yes.

00:38.445 --> 00:41.492
The object of the ceremony
is to transfer the power

00:41.535 --> 00:43.276
to a female next of kin.

00:43.320 --> 00:44.712
Am I a witch?

00:44.756 --> 00:46.497
You're my witch.

00:48.325 --> 00:50.892
[rain pattering]

00:50.936 --> 00:54.374
- Arjuna!

00:54.418 --> 00:57.377
Can you hear me?

00:57.420 --> 01:00.337
[dramatic music]

01:00.380 --> 01:02.730
Anyone!

01:02.774 --> 01:09.737
♪

01:13.219 --> 01:15.439
Arjuna!

01:15.482 --> 01:17.396
Get me out of here!

01:17.441 --> 01:20.270
[insects chirping]

01:23.751 --> 01:25.144
- [gasps]

01:25.188 --> 01:28.104
[breathing heavily]

01:34.197 --> 01:35.807
[gasps, exhales heavily]

01:40.246 --> 01:41.551
[gasps]

01:43.771 --> 01:45.425
[gasps]

01:45.469 --> 01:46.774
[liquid rippling]

01:46.818 --> 01:50.082
♪

01:50.126 --> 01:51.344
[gasps]

01:51.388 --> 01:54.259
[breathing heavily]

01:58.351 --> 01:59.831
[dog barking]

02:03.051 --> 02:04.096
[phone beeps]

02:04.140 --> 02:05.141
[tapping]

02:05.184 --> 02:06.751
[line ringing]

02:08.753 --> 02:10.146
- You've reached
Ciprien Grieve.

02:10.189 --> 02:12.103
Please leave a message.
[line beeps]

02:12.148 --> 02:14.280
- Hey, Sip,
I haven't heard from you.

02:14.324 --> 02:15.281
Can you call me back
when you get this?

02:15.325 --> 02:16.456
It's important.

02:29.774 --> 02:31.123
Are you there?

02:34.561 --> 02:37.173
Did you make this happen?

02:37.216 --> 02:39.392
♪

02:39.436 --> 02:40.872
- [grunting]
- Get off me!

02:40.915 --> 02:43.266
Ah! What are you doing?

02:43.309 --> 02:45.268
Stop, please!
- Shut up!

02:45.311 --> 02:47.705
- [sobbing] No!
- Shut up, witch!

02:47.748 --> 02:49.881
- So what did they use?

02:49.924 --> 02:52.144
Duct tape?
- No! No!

02:52.188 --> 02:53.189
- Yeah, that's right.

02:53.232 --> 02:56.844
♪

02:56.888 --> 02:59.020
And zip ties.

02:59.064 --> 03:01.980
[eerie music]

03:02.023 --> 03:04.852
♪

03:04.896 --> 03:07.812
- [grunting]

03:07.855 --> 03:14.819
♪

03:14.862 --> 03:16.734
[grunting, muffled shouting]

03:16.777 --> 03:19.563
[rustling]

03:19.606 --> 03:22.522
[grunting]

03:22.566 --> 03:25.482
[dramatic music]

03:25.525 --> 03:27.875
♪

03:29.399 --> 03:32.489
[eerie music]

03:32.531 --> 03:35.317
[voices whispering
indistinctly]

03:35.361 --> 03:38.712
♪

03:38.756 --> 03:42.499
- [vocalizing]

03:42.542 --> 03:49.245
♪

04:07.785 --> 04:09.265
[scraping]

04:27.761 --> 04:30.764
- When your coven gets
together,

04:30.808 --> 04:33.593
do you, like...

04:33.637 --> 04:34.638
call the corners?

04:37.641 --> 04:40.296
- [muffled speech]

04:42.689 --> 04:43.821
- Come here.

04:45.823 --> 04:46.780
Your face.

04:51.437 --> 04:52.743
- [sighs]

04:57.443 --> 04:58.792
- [gasps]

05:05.625 --> 05:06.582
[sighs]

05:08.149 --> 05:11.936
- W-what do you mean...
c-call the corners?

05:12.937 --> 05:14.504
- I saw it in a movie.

05:16.897 --> 05:18.595
- Do you like movies?

05:21.511 --> 05:23.382
I'm always looking

05:23.426 --> 05:26.864
for someone to go with me,
but...

05:29.780 --> 05:31.782
I can't go to the movies now.

05:34.393 --> 05:35.742
[inhales shakily]

05:35.786 --> 05:38.397
I could if you would help me.

05:38.441 --> 05:40.530
I wonder if you would help me.

05:43.446 --> 05:46.840
Help me open the cage.

05:46.884 --> 05:49.800
[tense music]

05:49.843 --> 05:52.933
♪

05:52.977 --> 05:54.718
- I'm not gonna do that.

06:00.114 --> 06:02.900
- [breathing shakily]

06:11.082 --> 06:12.213
- [sighs heavily]

06:14.302 --> 06:15.565
Is there a problem?

06:17.044 --> 06:19.438
- I just--I'm just looking
for Tessa.

06:19.482 --> 06:21.092
I need to talk to her.

06:22.049 --> 06:23.137
- Aren't you supposed to be
on a plane

06:23.181 --> 06:25.401
to San Francisco by now?

06:26.445 --> 06:29.579
- I-I need her to ask Lasher
a question for me.

06:31.537 --> 06:32.886
Please? It's important.

06:32.930 --> 06:35.236
- Fine. Wait here.

06:35.280 --> 06:38.239
[tense music]

06:38.283 --> 06:45.203
♪

06:46.291 --> 06:48.685
[creaking]

06:48.728 --> 06:51.209
- [sighs]

06:51.252 --> 06:58.129
♪

07:06.616 --> 07:09.532
[jazzy music]

07:09.575 --> 07:16.452
♪

07:46.569 --> 07:48.832
- You want a plate for that?

07:51.225 --> 07:53.184
- No, thank you. I'm fine.

07:54.707 --> 07:56.404
- Tessa's not in her room.

07:56.448 --> 07:58.972
Didn't even sleep in her bed.

07:59.016 --> 08:00.496
- Are you worried?

08:00.539 --> 08:03.107
- Probably went to a friend's.
I texted her.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.457
She'll answer
when she gets around to it.

08:05.501 --> 08:07.154
- Maybe we should check in
with her friends.

08:07.198 --> 08:09.287
- What is this "we"?
There is no we.

08:18.644 --> 08:20.864
- Sorry.
May I please use the bathroom?

08:25.433 --> 08:26.783
- You have no idea.

08:26.826 --> 08:29.655
My boss, she's all over me
all the time.

08:29.699 --> 08:32.136
But I've been in the business
a lot longer than her.

08:32.179 --> 08:34.660
But guess who makes
twice as much money.

08:36.096 --> 08:37.576
And guess
who's always leaving early

08:37.620 --> 08:38.708
for a date.

08:39.926 --> 08:42.233
- Don't you go on dates?

08:42.276 --> 08:44.496
- Nobody...

08:44.540 --> 08:47.020
wants to swipe right
on this face.

08:50.981 --> 08:52.678
- What's wrong with your face?

08:52.722 --> 08:55.638
[tense music]

08:55.681 --> 08:57.640
♪

08:57.683 --> 09:00.207
Show me.

09:00.251 --> 09:07.214
♪

09:20.097 --> 09:23.230
Let me see you.

09:23.274 --> 09:29.019
♪

09:29.062 --> 09:31.761
[voices whispering
indistinctly]

09:35.155 --> 09:37.288
[both gasping]

09:39.420 --> 09:40.900
[words echoing]
You're handsome.

09:43.816 --> 09:45.426
Anyone can see that.

09:48.560 --> 09:49.866
I can see it.

09:51.650 --> 09:55.045
I can see
you holding the key...

09:55.088 --> 09:56.742
[breathing shakily]

09:56.786 --> 10:01.965
Reaching out, using the key
to unlock the cage...

10:04.228 --> 10:05.969
So we can be closer together.

10:08.580 --> 10:12.105
[both breathing shakily]

10:22.681 --> 10:24.290
[rattling]

10:25.597 --> 10:27.991
- Keith! Arlo wants you.

10:28.034 --> 10:30.646
- [panting]

10:30.689 --> 10:31.647
[dark music]

10:31.690 --> 10:32.952
[bangs]

10:32.996 --> 10:35.999
[rattling]

10:36.042 --> 10:38.915
[breathing heavily]

10:38.958 --> 10:45.835
♪

10:47.750 --> 10:50.491
- [coughing]

10:50.535 --> 10:53.494
[panting]

10:55.105 --> 10:57.934
[sniffing]
[toilet flushing]

11:03.156 --> 11:04.288
[groans]

11:04.331 --> 11:07.204
[panting]

11:11.425 --> 11:12.949
[coughs]

11:13.689 --> 11:14.994
[sniffs]

11:18.781 --> 11:21.435
- It's a big day.

11:21.479 --> 11:23.089
Today we have a chance to get

11:23.133 --> 11:27.746
real, solid proof
of witchcraft.

11:27.790 --> 11:28.878
An actual witch on video.

11:28.921 --> 11:30.401
Nobody's ever caught that.

11:30.444 --> 11:34.318
And if we get it,
no more hiding in the shadows.

11:34.361 --> 11:36.973
We will take this movement
to the next level.

11:37.016 --> 11:39.758
And that's not
just any tarot-card-reading

11:39.802 --> 11:41.760
little Wiccan down there
either.

11:41.804 --> 11:43.153
That is a Mayfair.

11:43.196 --> 11:44.676
That is a legacy witch

11:44.720 --> 11:47.548
that our friend Keith here
introduced us to.

11:47.592 --> 11:49.072
[dramatic music]

11:49.115 --> 11:50.551
She's the real deal.

11:50.595 --> 11:52.336
♪

11:52.379 --> 11:56.253
- So, uh, how are we gonna...

11:57.820 --> 11:59.299
- The old-fashioned way,
Keith.

11:59.343 --> 12:02.259
Threat of death.

12:02.302 --> 12:06.176
The only thing that ever drew
the truth out of a witch.

12:06.219 --> 12:07.873
Fire.

12:07.917 --> 12:10.615
- We don't have the right fuel.
- Excuse me?

12:10.658 --> 12:13.792
- Lighter fluid and gasoline
is gonna leave bone behind.

12:13.836 --> 12:15.533
Now, what we need
is some thermite.

12:17.187 --> 12:18.971
I know where to get some.

12:19.015 --> 12:20.233
- Go get it.

12:20.277 --> 12:21.757
♪

12:21.800 --> 12:23.889
- I can do that.

12:23.933 --> 12:26.370
- Some kind of
industrial building.

12:26.413 --> 12:28.415
She saw Tessa being tied up.

12:28.459 --> 12:31.201
They had buckets of gasoline.

12:31.244 --> 12:32.463
She didn't come home
last night.

12:32.506 --> 12:33.769
I tried to track her.

12:33.812 --> 12:36.075
It didn't work.

12:36.119 --> 12:38.077
Now she's not answering
her phone.

12:38.121 --> 12:40.558
Something's definitely wrong.
- We'll get help.

12:40.601 --> 12:42.299
I promise. Take a breath.

12:42.342 --> 12:45.171
- Hey, what's going on?
- We'll figure it out.

12:45.215 --> 12:47.434
- Jojo had a premonition
about Tessa.

12:47.478 --> 12:49.262
- Cortland's coming.
He's picking up Alonso.

12:49.306 --> 12:51.134
- Good.

12:51.177 --> 12:53.310
- Don't worry.
Alonso will find her.

12:53.353 --> 12:55.486
- How could Tessa be
in trouble?

12:55.529 --> 12:57.053
Lasher's with her.

12:58.881 --> 13:00.056
- [grunts]
[bars clanging]

13:00.099 --> 13:01.318
[pants]

13:02.798 --> 13:04.800
[crying]

13:04.843 --> 13:07.237
[bars clanging]

13:07.280 --> 13:08.499
[sniffs, exhales sharply]

13:12.155 --> 13:14.679
[sniffs, panting]

13:17.116 --> 13:22.426
♪

13:22.469 --> 13:25.472
[crying]

13:35.918 --> 13:38.616
[whispering] Lasher...

13:42.838 --> 13:44.970
Lasher.

13:45.014 --> 13:46.798
Lasher, please...

13:49.018 --> 13:50.367
[sniffles]

13:50.410 --> 13:52.543
Why won't you come to me?

13:55.459 --> 13:57.461
You chose me.

13:57.504 --> 14:00.377
[crying]

14:10.213 --> 14:11.736
- Wake up.

14:14.173 --> 14:15.566
Wake up.

14:18.308 --> 14:19.700
- If you...

14:19.744 --> 14:22.399
sound...

14:22.442 --> 14:27.012
we can help guide you out.

14:27.056 --> 14:29.972
[dramatic music]

14:30.015 --> 14:31.495
♪

14:31.538 --> 14:34.890
If you can hear
the sound of my voice...

14:34.933 --> 14:41.853
♪

14:41.897 --> 14:43.028
- I hear you, Arjuna.

14:43.072 --> 14:44.595
- Please listen.
- I hear you.

14:44.638 --> 14:47.467
- We can guide you out.

14:47.511 --> 14:50.862
Ciprien,
we can try and help you.

14:52.777 --> 14:55.432
It's Arjuna.

14:55.475 --> 14:58.739
You are trapped in a memory.

14:58.783 --> 15:01.177
The object that you used
to enter the memory

15:01.220 --> 15:03.570
is no longer here
with your body.

15:03.614 --> 15:04.963
- The necklace.
- The only way out

15:05.007 --> 15:06.922
is the way you came in.

15:06.965 --> 15:09.707
You have to find that necklace.

15:09.750 --> 15:13.537
It is your portal.
There is no other way.

15:13.580 --> 15:17.454
No other way apart from death.

15:17.497 --> 15:19.630
- The witch hunter.

15:23.503 --> 15:24.983
- She came to me yesterday.

15:25.027 --> 15:27.246
She was very upset about
some guys on the Internet.

15:27.290 --> 15:29.161
She said that they had stolen
Deirdre's heart

15:29.205 --> 15:31.381
and she wanted
to confront them.

15:31.424 --> 15:33.557
So maybe that's what she did.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.559
- Why'd she come to you?

15:35.602 --> 15:37.474
- Because
she was the designee then.

15:37.517 --> 15:40.129
Because she had Lasher.

15:40.172 --> 15:41.652
[sighs] Oh, Tessa.

15:43.045 --> 15:44.960
This is your fault.

15:45.003 --> 15:46.744
You should have gone to get
your own mother's heart.

15:46.787 --> 15:48.224
- I didn't ask her
to do anything.

15:48.267 --> 15:50.748
- You wouldn't help her,
so she went alone,

15:50.791 --> 15:52.576
thinking he had her back.

15:52.619 --> 15:54.491
But he's not with her.

15:54.534 --> 15:56.972
He's still with you.
- He's not.

15:57.015 --> 15:58.974
I haven't seen him
since the ceremony.

16:00.192 --> 16:02.499
- Call him. Let's make sure.

16:03.674 --> 16:06.155
- When I try to speak to him,
I-I get nothing.

16:06.198 --> 16:07.721
No response.

16:07.765 --> 16:09.158
- Call him.

16:10.768 --> 16:12.639
Use the words.

16:12.683 --> 16:14.380
[tense music]

16:14.424 --> 16:17.862
- I think that would be
like inviting him back into me.

16:17.905 --> 16:20.212
And what if he's with her
and she needs him

16:20.256 --> 16:22.258
and-and I call him away?

16:22.301 --> 16:23.868
♪

16:23.911 --> 16:25.087
- Okay, forgive me.

16:25.130 --> 16:26.479
Why are you even here?

16:26.523 --> 16:28.307
Didn't we all just go
to great lengths

16:28.351 --> 16:31.441
so you can bail on this family?

16:31.484 --> 16:34.009
- You wanted to ask him
a question, right?

16:34.052 --> 16:36.881
What was so pressing?
What did you need to ask?

16:38.100 --> 16:39.971
- That's not important now.

16:40.015 --> 16:42.234
- Uh-uh.

16:42.278 --> 16:44.062
She's a goddamn liar.

16:44.106 --> 16:45.803
[door opens]

16:45.846 --> 16:47.718
- Alonso, let's set you up
in the library.

16:47.761 --> 16:50.025
- Alonso's here.
- [sighs]

16:50.068 --> 16:56.988
♪

17:02.819 --> 17:05.692
[dramatic music]

17:05.736 --> 17:12.699
♪

17:27.845 --> 17:30.717
[dog whining]

17:33.198 --> 17:35.070
- [sighs]

17:41.424 --> 17:42.425
- You can see me?

17:46.690 --> 17:53.566
♪

17:59.833 --> 18:03.098
- [groaning]

18:05.012 --> 18:07.580
- He's an--a scry.

18:07.624 --> 18:10.148
[blood dripping]

18:10.192 --> 18:14.021
He's found people
for the police, the FBI,

18:14.065 --> 18:15.371
even the Talamasca.

18:16.807 --> 18:18.069
He'll find her.

18:23.161 --> 18:24.771
I hope I'm wrong.

18:24.815 --> 18:26.425
But as visions go,
it was very clear.

18:31.082 --> 18:32.997
- [whimpers]
- This may sting.

18:35.042 --> 18:36.131
- Could you see
what time of day it was

18:36.174 --> 18:37.958
in your vision?

18:38.002 --> 18:39.656
- You mean how much time
do we have to get to her?

18:41.310 --> 18:42.572
I couldn't tell.

18:42.615 --> 18:49.231
♪

18:52.364 --> 18:56.151
- Um, tell me truly, cher,

18:56.194 --> 19:02.157
between us, um, is he with you?

19:03.549 --> 19:05.247
- No.

19:05.290 --> 19:07.249
- Ah.

19:07.292 --> 19:11.209
If he's not with her
and he's not with you,

19:11.253 --> 19:15.126
then, um, where is he?

19:16.606 --> 19:18.173
- I really don't know.

19:19.826 --> 19:21.915
- Was he angry with you?

19:21.959 --> 19:23.526
Can you call him?

19:25.223 --> 19:26.703
- [groans]

19:29.271 --> 19:32.143
[breathing heavily]

19:35.842 --> 19:37.366
I'm not getting anything.

19:39.063 --> 19:40.020
It's muddy.

19:41.718 --> 19:43.720
This happens when there are
too many blood ties.

19:43.763 --> 19:45.200
The signal is confused.

19:46.201 --> 19:47.724
- I always said you had
too many kids, Leesh.

19:51.249 --> 19:53.338
- I'm so sorry.

19:53.382 --> 19:54.557
- Use my blood.

19:56.080 --> 19:57.951
- The way it works
is close blood ties.

19:57.995 --> 19:59.953
- Use me to find
my mother's heart.

19:59.997 --> 20:01.781
I'm her only child.

20:01.825 --> 20:03.696
And wherever that heart is,
that's where Tessa is, right?

20:06.482 --> 20:08.223
Could that work?

20:08.266 --> 20:09.485
- Let's find out.

20:11.008 --> 20:13.053
- Help! Help!

20:13.097 --> 20:14.968
Help! Anybody!
- Why isn't she gagged?

20:15.012 --> 20:17.232
- Must have gotten it off
somehow.

20:18.320 --> 20:20.539
- Anyone who can hear me,
please--ow, no!

20:20.583 --> 20:24.021
No! [screaming]

20:24.064 --> 20:26.197
No!

20:26.241 --> 20:27.851
- No, no, no. Leave it off.
Leave it off.

20:27.894 --> 20:30.245
We can get every word on video.

20:30.288 --> 20:31.855
- What kind of magic
can you do, girl?

20:31.898 --> 20:33.944
- I can't do magic.
Magic isn't real.

20:33.987 --> 20:36.860
- [chuckles] That's funny.

20:36.903 --> 20:39.166
She'll show us soon enough.
Come on.

20:39.210 --> 20:41.343
- No. Help!

20:41.386 --> 20:42.735
- [grunts]
- Help! Please!

20:42.779 --> 20:45.129
No! No!

20:45.172 --> 20:46.739
Stop! Help! Please!

20:46.783 --> 20:48.611
Help me, Keith.
Keith, this isn't you.

20:48.654 --> 20:51.701
Please don't do this.
You don't have to do this!

20:51.744 --> 20:54.356
[screams] Ow! Ow, ow.

20:54.399 --> 20:56.009
No!

20:56.053 --> 20:57.576
Can anyone hear me?

20:57.620 --> 20:58.447
[restraints click]

20:58.490 --> 20:59.883
- Got her?

20:59.926 --> 21:01.276
- Can anyone hear me?

21:02.886 --> 21:04.279
[screaming] Help!

21:06.324 --> 21:09.240
- [grunting]

21:09.284 --> 21:16.160
♪

21:20.295 --> 21:21.948
- [gasps]

21:23.559 --> 21:25.169
How far along are you?

21:28.477 --> 21:29.434
- [groans]

21:33.482 --> 21:36.006
[groaning]

21:36.049 --> 21:38.835
[breathing heavily]

21:40.489 --> 21:41.446
[liquid sloshing]

21:41.490 --> 21:48.540
♪

21:49.019 --> 21:50.368
- It's so clear.

21:50.412 --> 21:52.718
- The connection was strong.

21:52.762 --> 21:54.329
She's just across the bridge

21:54.372 --> 21:55.765
in that wild bit
of Jean Lafitte.

21:59.421 --> 22:01.205
- [whispering] She's pregnant.

22:04.643 --> 22:07.429
- Let's split into groups
and we'll each search an area.

22:07.472 --> 22:09.169
- Since when are you in charge?

22:09.213 --> 22:11.258
- I'm not.

22:11.302 --> 22:12.695
But it's my fault
she's out there,

22:12.738 --> 22:14.653
and I wanna make it right.

22:14.697 --> 22:17.526
[crows cawing]

22:28.058 --> 22:30.582
[bleating]

22:30.626 --> 22:33.498
[soft music]

22:33.542 --> 22:35.413
♪

22:35.457 --> 22:38.373
[eerie vocalizing]

22:38.416 --> 22:42.420
♪

22:42.464 --> 22:45.467
[fire crackling]

22:45.510 --> 22:48.383
♪

22:48.426 --> 22:50.210
- Suzanne.

22:50.254 --> 22:53.300
[dramatic music]

22:53.344 --> 22:55.215
You have the necklace?

22:57.479 --> 23:03.485
♪

23:18.108 --> 23:20.937
- [chuckling]

23:29.598 --> 23:31.251
- Keep your phones on,
everybody.

23:31.295 --> 23:32.775
And please speed.

23:32.818 --> 23:34.603
They're looking for proof.

23:34.646 --> 23:36.387
If they find it,
they will be coming for us all.

23:36.431 --> 23:37.780
- Tessa knows that.

23:37.823 --> 23:39.216
She would never give up
the family.

23:39.259 --> 23:40.826
- [sighs]
- If you get to her first,

23:40.870 --> 23:42.741
text the thread.
Do not go in alone.

23:42.785 --> 23:45.004
We need to go in all at once,
a united front,

23:45.048 --> 23:46.876
so this can be quick
and bloodless.

23:49.008 --> 23:51.402
- Rowan. A word?

23:52.708 --> 23:56.146
Now, cher,
I know you wanna help.

23:56.189 --> 23:57.887
But the best help
you can give right now

23:57.930 --> 24:00.455
is to call on him right here,
right now,

24:00.498 --> 24:02.282
and let him guide you.
- I'm not gonna do that.

24:02.326 --> 24:04.067
I've already explained--
- No, no, no.

24:04.110 --> 24:05.895
Think of your cousin.

24:05.938 --> 24:07.505
- I'm thinking of her.
That's why--

24:07.549 --> 24:09.942
- No, no, no, listen to me.
You must call him.

24:12.423 --> 24:14.469
- Take your hands off me.

24:14.512 --> 24:17.428
[tense music]

24:17.472 --> 24:21.127
♪

24:21.171 --> 24:22.477
[voices whispering
indistinctly]

24:29.919 --> 24:32.487
- [sighs] I--

24:32.530 --> 24:34.924
What was that?

24:34.967 --> 24:37.796
- Stay with him. He needs you.

24:37.840 --> 24:40.799
[keys jingling]

24:40.843 --> 24:41.800
[sighs]

24:44.107 --> 24:45.587
[door closes]

24:45.630 --> 24:48.981
♪

24:49.025 --> 24:51.941
[Lasher laughing]

24:58.251 --> 24:59.557
There's no way out.

24:59.601 --> 25:01.472
You're not in a human memory.

25:04.649 --> 25:07.173
- Is this what happened to you?

25:07.217 --> 25:09.524
- Ah, you're the only person
here.

25:11.438 --> 25:12.788
- This is your memory?

25:15.355 --> 25:17.967
You lured me here,
and you trapped me.

25:18.010 --> 25:21.666
- No. You did this to yourself.

25:21.710 --> 25:22.841
Let's play a game.

25:24.669 --> 25:27.585
[sighs]

25:27.629 --> 25:30.327
Let's see what happens...

25:30.370 --> 25:31.720
- [gasps]

25:31.763 --> 25:35.332
- If you die here,
will you die there?

25:35.375 --> 25:36.855
- If you wanted me dead,

25:36.899 --> 25:40.032
you'd have done it weeks ago,
in the house.

25:40.076 --> 25:42.034
But you didn't.

25:42.078 --> 25:45.603
You let me go.
- No. She let you go.

25:45.647 --> 25:47.213
You'd served your purpose.

25:47.257 --> 25:48.432
- [gasps]

25:56.266 --> 25:57.746
- She's pregnant.

26:03.186 --> 26:05.710
- Then let me go to her,

26:05.754 --> 26:07.843
take care of her.

26:07.886 --> 26:11.150
If I've served my purpose,
why keep me here?

26:11.194 --> 26:12.630
I am no threat to you, right?

26:12.674 --> 26:14.066
- She doesn't want you.

26:15.372 --> 26:17.026
She doesn't
wanna be domesticated.

26:17.069 --> 26:19.158
Why would a lion want
to be a house cat?

26:19.202 --> 26:20.507
- I would never do that
to her.

26:20.551 --> 26:22.727
- Of course you would.
[chuckles]

26:22.771 --> 26:23.598
You already have.

26:25.687 --> 26:27.210
You wanna control that power.

26:27.253 --> 26:31.214
You want to suppress
her true desires,

26:31.257 --> 26:34.043
to conform
to your basic human morality.

26:34.086 --> 26:36.698
- While you force your way
into her head,

26:36.741 --> 26:38.525
force her to commit
to your will.

26:38.569 --> 26:41.746
- No, I enact her wishes,
and she wishes for power.

26:41.790 --> 26:43.661
- If you're willing
to give her power,

26:43.705 --> 26:45.968
it is only because
her power will strengthen you.

26:46.011 --> 26:48.927
- Of course it will.

26:48.971 --> 26:52.017
I am a part of her
just as she's a part of me.

26:52.061 --> 26:53.453
We're bound together.

26:53.497 --> 26:55.804
[sighs]

26:55.847 --> 26:58.545
She doesn't see it yet,
but she will.

26:58.589 --> 27:00.635
And in her hour
of greatest need,

27:00.678 --> 27:02.637
it's me that she will call for.

27:03.289 --> 27:04.421
- What have you done?

27:04.464 --> 27:06.162
[grunts]

27:14.779 --> 27:15.780
- What do you think
will happen to you

27:15.824 --> 27:17.477
when I leave?

27:17.521 --> 27:20.132
[door creaking]

27:20.176 --> 27:22.700
[tense music]

27:22.744 --> 27:24.484
Will you still exist?

27:24.528 --> 27:26.791
♪

27:26.835 --> 27:29.054
Will any of this?

27:29.098 --> 27:31.578
- Don't let her die.

27:31.622 --> 27:34.843
- You should have stayed away.

27:34.886 --> 27:36.192
But even as a little boy,

27:36.235 --> 27:37.628
you couldn't help yourself,
could you?

27:37.672 --> 27:39.674
♪

27:39.717 --> 27:42.241
You had to walk by the house.

27:42.285 --> 27:44.679
You had to know
what was happening inside.

27:44.722 --> 27:47.638
[dramatic music]

27:47.682 --> 27:48.813
♪

27:48.857 --> 27:49.945
Goodbye, Ciprien.

27:52.295 --> 27:56.125
- [screaming]

27:56.168 --> 27:58.170
♪

27:58.214 --> 28:01.347
[sighs] Lasher...

28:01.391 --> 28:08.311
♪

28:09.486 --> 28:12.228
[voices chanting indistinctly]

28:20.105 --> 28:22.238
Something's changed.

28:29.724 --> 28:31.987
- Hey.

28:32.030 --> 28:35.164
Hey. Hey.

28:35.207 --> 28:37.906
M-my family, we're not--

28:37.949 --> 28:41.257
[sighs] We're not witches,
but we do have money.

28:43.563 --> 28:47.045
And if you help me,
I can help you.

28:48.438 --> 28:49.874
Woman to woman.

28:59.144 --> 29:01.930
- You, uh--
you know what this place is?

29:03.540 --> 29:05.107
Mayfair Auto Parts.

29:06.891 --> 29:10.677
Glen and me spent 17 years here

29:10.721 --> 29:13.419
putting car parts
into cardboard.

29:16.205 --> 29:19.686
Then you shut us down...

29:19.730 --> 29:21.253
outsourced our jobs.

29:21.297 --> 29:24.343
Woke up one morning,
didn't have a paycheck,

29:24.387 --> 29:26.432
didn't have health insurance.

29:30.567 --> 29:35.354
Our daughter Jenny
was at your hospital...

29:35.398 --> 29:37.792
halfway through
her chemotherapy.

29:37.835 --> 29:40.751
[somber music]

29:40.795 --> 29:44.320
♪

29:44.363 --> 29:48.846
- I'm-I'm so sorry,
but that wasn't me.

29:48.890 --> 29:51.718
- It was your family.

29:51.762 --> 29:54.678
You profited off it, right?

29:56.636 --> 29:58.029
Yeah.

29:58.073 --> 30:00.466
So woman to woman...

30:00.510 --> 30:02.860
[tense music]

30:02.904 --> 30:04.601
You are on your own.

30:04.644 --> 30:07.343
♪

30:07.386 --> 30:09.388
- [panting]

30:09.432 --> 30:12.130
- [grunting]

30:12.174 --> 30:18.136
♪

30:18.180 --> 30:20.443
[jars clinking]

30:20.486 --> 30:26.275
♪

30:26.318 --> 30:27.319
Henbane.

30:27.363 --> 30:34.326
♪

30:47.513 --> 30:49.254
[sighs]

30:49.298 --> 30:52.344
[eerie vocalizing]

30:52.388 --> 30:55.347
[slurping]

30:55.391 --> 30:58.307
[coughing]

30:58.350 --> 31:01.658
♪

31:01.701 --> 31:04.574
[gasping]

31:09.361 --> 31:12.538
[high-pitched whining]

31:12.582 --> 31:17.848
♪

31:17.892 --> 31:20.807
- Nice and easy.
Come back nice and slow.

31:20.851 --> 31:23.854
- [sighs]
- You found the necklace.

31:27.118 --> 31:30.078
- Henbane. [gasping]

31:30.121 --> 31:32.341
- Henbane!

31:32.384 --> 31:34.125
You died in the memory?

31:34.169 --> 31:35.910
- [vomiting]

31:35.953 --> 31:39.435
[coughing]

31:39.478 --> 31:42.438
Aw. [grunts]

31:42.481 --> 31:45.702
I have to get to--[groans]

31:45.745 --> 31:47.965
I have to get to her now.

31:48.009 --> 31:50.925
- Ciprien...
- [groaning]

31:52.970 --> 31:54.798
- Stay here.

31:54.841 --> 31:56.060
- Thank you.

31:56.104 --> 32:02.719
♪

32:02.762 --> 32:05.591
- What the hell came over you?

32:05.635 --> 32:08.290
[tense music]

32:08.333 --> 32:10.945
- Jojo, dear, would you get me
a glass of water?

32:10.988 --> 32:17.908
♪

32:24.088 --> 32:27.091
[tapping]

32:27.135 --> 32:29.964
[line ringing]

32:30.007 --> 32:31.791
She's pregnant.

32:31.835 --> 32:32.879
As soon as I heard,
I tried to get her

32:32.923 --> 32:34.098
to call out to him,

32:34.142 --> 32:36.057
but she insisted on going
to the woods

32:36.100 --> 32:38.494
to rescue her foolish cousin.

32:38.537 --> 32:40.191
I need you to handle this.

32:40.235 --> 32:43.020
Now.
- I'll take care of it.

32:43.064 --> 32:44.108
- She's gone out to look
for her

32:44.152 --> 32:45.675
somewhere in the Jean Lafitte.

32:45.718 --> 32:48.460
- Hmm. I know the area.

32:48.504 --> 32:51.028
We had eyes on an event
that may have precipitated

32:51.072 --> 32:53.465
this unfortunate situation.

32:55.076 --> 32:56.947
- Oh, good.

32:56.991 --> 32:58.601
But once you find her,

32:58.644 --> 33:00.472
you do
what you Talamasca do best.

33:01.299 --> 33:02.822
- I'll take it from here.

33:06.000 --> 33:07.697
- Sir...

33:07.740 --> 33:10.439
Rowan Mayfair is in trouble.

33:10.482 --> 33:13.007
Lasher was trying
to keep me away from her.

33:13.050 --> 33:14.704
Um, something is happening
right now,

33:14.747 --> 33:15.966
but I don't know where.

33:16.010 --> 33:18.664
- Good thing I do. I'll drive.

33:18.708 --> 33:25.454
♪

33:28.022 --> 33:30.720
- Turn left at the stop sign.

33:30.763 --> 33:32.852
Turn left.

33:32.896 --> 33:34.898
[crow cawing]

33:40.599 --> 33:42.340
- Is this you?

33:42.384 --> 33:44.429
♪

33:44.473 --> 33:47.258
[crow cawing]

33:47.302 --> 33:50.174
[disquieting music]

33:50.218 --> 33:52.350
♪

33:52.393 --> 33:54.525
- Turn left.

33:54.570 --> 33:56.311
- Sir, can you go any faster?

33:56.353 --> 33:59.313
- You know,
I'm impressed with you, son.

33:59.357 --> 34:02.491
You put yourself on the line
for this case again and again.

34:02.534 --> 34:03.927
I didn't know you possessed

34:03.969 --> 34:06.060
this kind of commitment
to the work.

34:06.712 --> 34:07.887
I think you're ready.

34:09.715 --> 34:11.761
- Ready for what?
- Did you know

34:11.804 --> 34:13.893
that when the Talamasca
was a young organization,

34:13.937 --> 34:18.072
several European chapters had
their own agents killed

34:18.114 --> 34:20.509
if they failed to keep
confidentiality

34:20.552 --> 34:22.424
or demonstrated
supernatural giftedness

34:22.467 --> 34:23.902
in any public way?

34:23.947 --> 34:25.949
Killed.

34:25.992 --> 34:27.603
Can you imagine?
Of such priority

34:27.646 --> 34:29.866
was the mission to hide
the supernatural

34:29.909 --> 34:31.694
from those
who would condemn it--

34:31.737 --> 34:35.306
the Church, of course,
at that time,

34:35.350 --> 34:36.873
the Templars, certainly--
- Sir...

34:36.916 --> 34:38.483
could you please drive
a little faster?

34:38.527 --> 34:40.137
- Well, there's no need.

34:40.181 --> 34:41.443
We're here.

34:46.796 --> 34:49.364
- We're not gonna save
your girlfriend this evening.

34:49.407 --> 34:51.583
She's gonna save herself.

34:51.627 --> 34:54.891
[tense music]

34:54.934 --> 34:59.417
♪

34:59.461 --> 35:01.680
- What is this?

35:01.724 --> 35:04.118
If we don't get to her now,
she's gonna call down Lasher.

35:04.161 --> 35:06.163
- That's right.

35:06.816 --> 35:09.210
- What the--
- The deep truth,

35:09.253 --> 35:10.733
the one I want you
to really hear,

35:10.776 --> 35:13.823
is that our highest purpose
is to watch--

35:13.866 --> 35:15.390
to make record
of the supernatural forces

35:15.433 --> 35:16.913
that shape our world,

35:16.956 --> 35:18.393
for such time
as action may be necessary.

35:18.436 --> 35:20.830
- Action is necessary
right the fuck now.

35:20.873 --> 35:23.049
- Change can be difficult.

35:23.093 --> 35:24.094
You've gotten caught up
in this.

35:24.138 --> 35:25.356
You need to step back.

35:25.400 --> 35:27.228
To watch, Ciprien,
that's our job.

35:30.231 --> 35:31.667
- You're in this with Lasher.

35:33.756 --> 35:36.106
You're a part of this.

35:36.150 --> 35:37.368
- If she makes the choice

35:37.412 --> 35:39.936
that we believe
she's gonna make,

35:39.979 --> 35:43.113
she's about to fulfill
a very old prophecy.

35:43.157 --> 35:44.984
And a new era will begin.

35:45.028 --> 35:46.551
- What prophecy?

35:46.595 --> 35:47.770
What are you talking about?

35:47.813 --> 35:49.598
What's going to happen to her?

35:49.641 --> 35:52.209
♪

35:52.253 --> 35:55.125
[breathing heavily]

35:55.169 --> 35:58.607
♪

35:58.650 --> 35:59.999
Damn it!

36:00.043 --> 36:01.784
- Wait! No, stop.

36:01.827 --> 36:03.612
Please don't do this.

36:03.655 --> 36:06.267
Don't do this. I'm not a witch.

36:06.310 --> 36:08.007
Keith...

36:08.051 --> 36:10.227
Keith, look at me.
I-I-I'm not a witch.

36:10.271 --> 36:11.837
Please, I'm just a girl.

36:11.881 --> 36:13.926
- All set?

36:13.970 --> 36:15.667
- Don't you see
there's no way--

36:15.711 --> 36:17.452
there is no way for me to prove

36:17.495 --> 36:18.931
I'm not what you think I am.
- Shh, shh.

36:18.975 --> 36:20.672
[lighter clicks]

36:20.716 --> 36:22.108
[dramatic music]

36:22.152 --> 36:23.109
- We're gonna give you
one chance

36:23.153 --> 36:24.459
to do the right thing.

36:24.502 --> 36:27.723
♪

36:27.766 --> 36:29.290
Show us your magic.

36:29.333 --> 36:36.210
♪

36:37.254 --> 36:38.690
- I'm not a witch.

36:39.691 --> 36:40.997
You're making a mistake.

36:42.259 --> 36:43.434
- You're lying.

36:43.478 --> 36:46.002
We all heard you call out
to someone

36:46.045 --> 36:47.786
out in those woods.
- That was a prayer

36:47.830 --> 36:50.354
my mother taught me.
- Oh, a prayer? Good.

36:50.398 --> 36:52.835
Well, if you worship God,
then come clean.

36:52.878 --> 36:54.706
- [sighs]

36:54.750 --> 37:01.713
♪

37:20.732 --> 37:22.430
- No!

37:22.473 --> 37:25.041
It doesn't prove anything!
I'm begging you.

37:25.084 --> 37:27.783
Please.

37:27.826 --> 37:30.873
- All right, that's it.

37:30.916 --> 37:32.527
You're giving us
no other choice.

37:32.570 --> 37:35.094
♪

37:35.138 --> 37:36.879
All right, do it.

37:36.922 --> 37:38.097
- No!

37:39.751 --> 37:41.666
[sobs]

37:41.710 --> 37:44.321
- [groaning]

37:44.365 --> 37:46.192
- Rodney?
- What the hell?

37:46.236 --> 37:48.891
- [grunting]

37:48.934 --> 37:55.811
♪

37:57.029 --> 38:00.163
- [grunting]

38:03.384 --> 38:04.950
- Ahh, it's her!

38:04.994 --> 38:07.431
She's doing it. She's doing it!

38:08.127 --> 38:09.128
- Arlo...

38:09.825 --> 38:11.130
- [groans]

38:12.828 --> 38:14.090
- Help me...

38:14.133 --> 38:15.961
- I never wanted any of this.

38:16.005 --> 38:22.359
♪

38:22.403 --> 38:24.709
- Ahh! No, please!

38:24.753 --> 38:28.147
[coughing] No!

38:28.191 --> 38:31.629
♪

38:31.673 --> 38:32.848
[gunshot]

38:32.891 --> 38:34.458
- [grunts]
- No!

38:34.502 --> 38:35.764
[sobbing]

38:38.984 --> 38:42.031
- [gasping]
- Rowan, get up!

38:42.074 --> 38:44.381
I can't breathe! Hurry!

38:44.425 --> 38:47.341
[sobbing]

38:48.907 --> 38:51.954
No! Get up!

38:51.997 --> 38:54.391
Rowan, please hurry!

38:54.435 --> 38:57.220
Hurry! I can't breathe!

38:57.263 --> 38:59.396
- Tessa...

38:59.440 --> 39:01.703
- [gasping]
- Tessa...

39:01.746 --> 39:04.532
- [coughing]

39:04.575 --> 39:06.403
- I got you.
- [coughing]

39:06.447 --> 39:07.361
- Come on.

39:12.322 --> 39:13.976
- Thank you. Thank you.

39:15.412 --> 39:19.285
This is--[coughs]
This is yours.

39:19.329 --> 39:22.027
Take it, please.

39:22.071 --> 39:23.028
- Fucking witch!

39:23.072 --> 39:24.421
[gunshot]

39:24.465 --> 39:27.381
[both grunt]
[gun clicking]

39:27.424 --> 39:30.166
[dramatic music]

39:30.209 --> 39:32.037
- Tessa.

39:32.081 --> 39:36.477
♪

39:36.520 --> 39:39.044
Tessa.
- Don't let him get away.

39:39.088 --> 39:42.047
♪

39:42.091 --> 39:43.832
- Tessa. Tessa!

39:43.875 --> 39:45.442
♪

39:45.486 --> 39:48.227
No. Tessa.

39:48.271 --> 39:51.100
[fire crackling]

40:06.550 --> 40:08.596
Mi Daemon, ad me veni!

40:08.639 --> 40:11.294
Mi Daemon, mihi labora!

40:11.337 --> 40:14.123
Mi Daemon, me libera!

40:14.166 --> 40:15.690
[Goat's "Let It Burn"]

40:15.733 --> 40:21.913
- ♪ The sky lights up
once again ♪

40:21.957 --> 40:26.483
♪ Like sunrise rode
at his fall ♪

40:26.527 --> 40:30.531
♪ You know this

40:30.574 --> 40:33.011
♪

40:33.055 --> 40:34.578
♪ You showed me

40:34.622 --> 40:39.235
♪ It's that time once again

40:39.278 --> 40:40.889
♪

40:40.932 --> 40:45.502
♪ When plants reflect
in your eyes ♪

40:45.546 --> 40:48.549
♪ You know it

40:52.335 --> 40:53.641
On the next episode
of "Mayfair Witches"...

40:53.684 --> 40:55.338
♪

40:55.381 --> 40:57.079
Find him!

40:57.122 --> 41:00.648
♪

41:00.691 --> 41:02.345
I'm trying to get in touch
with my brother Ciprien.

41:02.388 --> 41:04.086
There's nobody here
by that name.

41:04.129 --> 41:06.915
♪

41:06.958 --> 41:07.916
Rowan.

41:07.959 --> 41:09.657
What's going on?

41:09.700 --> 41:11.485
Come.

41:11.528 --> 41:13.182
[Grunts]

41:13.225 --> 41:20.798
♪

41:22.191 --> 41:28.502
♪

41:28.545 --> 41:31.809
Ciprien: Arjuna!

41:31.853 --> 41:33.507
Can you hear me?

41:33.550 --> 41:35.465
Spalding: Cip has no idea
what's happening to him.

41:35.509 --> 41:38.599
He's never touched something
and gone into the memory.

41:38.642 --> 41:40.296
It's really terrifying

41:40.339 --> 41:43.125
to still be here,
to not be able to get out.

41:43.168 --> 41:45.170
He can't get himself
back to reality.

41:46.171 --> 41:47.912
Arjuna!

41:47.956 --> 41:49.653
Get me out of here!

41:49.697 --> 41:53.439
And he's seen what Lasher has
done to this village,

41:53.483 --> 41:55.441
the flames
that have consumed it.

41:55.485 --> 41:57.748
Spalding: He knows that
in some way, the state he's in,

41:57.792 --> 41:59.794
and this village,
is due to Lasher.

41:59.837 --> 42:02.536
And I think he knows that some
things can interact with him.

42:06.017 --> 42:07.497
You can see me?

42:11.936 --> 42:14.635
Florie and Suzanne
are harbingers

42:14.678 --> 42:16.680
of Lasher being in this world.

42:16.724 --> 42:18.987
It's Lasher who's allowing them
to see him.

42:19.030 --> 42:20.597
It's Lasher
whose memory he's in,

42:20.641 --> 42:22.338
and it's not operating like

42:22.381 --> 42:24.253
the kind of memory
that he's used to.

42:24.296 --> 42:28.170
[Laughing]

42:29.127 --> 42:31.608
[Gasps][Clicking tongue]

42:31.652 --> 42:33.131
You lured me here.

42:33.175 --> 42:34.350
And you trapped me.

42:34.393 --> 42:35.656
No.

42:35.699 --> 42:37.266
You did this to yourself.

42:37.309 --> 42:40.835
Cip really has absolutely no way
to combat Lasher.

42:40.878 --> 42:43.098
Let's see what happens.

42:43.141 --> 42:44.621
[Gasps, shudders]

42:44.665 --> 42:46.492
If you die here...

42:46.536 --> 42:47.972
will you die there?

42:48.016 --> 42:50.018
[Shakily]
If you wanted me dead,

42:50.061 --> 42:52.411
you'd have done it weeks ago,
in the house.

42:52.455 --> 42:54.892
But you didn't.

42:54.936 --> 42:57.329
You let me go.

42:57.373 --> 42:58.722
Shelet you go.

42:58.766 --> 43:00.550
You'd served your purpose.

43:00.594 --> 43:04.293
Cip thinks that Lasher
is absolutely evil,

43:04.336 --> 43:06.817
that Lasher is controlling
Rowan's mind,

43:06.861 --> 43:08.079
manipulating Rowan.

43:08.123 --> 43:10.342
Forced your way
into her head.

43:10.386 --> 43:12.214
Force her to commit
to your will.

43:12.257 --> 43:13.955
No, I enact her wishes.

43:13.998 --> 43:15.434
And she wishes for power.

43:15.478 --> 43:17.219
If you're willing
to give her power,

43:17.262 --> 43:19.743
it is only because her power
will strengthen you.

43:19.787 --> 43:22.224
Of course it will.

43:22.267 --> 43:25.531
I am a part of her,
just as she's a part of me.

43:25.575 --> 43:27.403
We're bound together.

43:27.446 --> 43:30.014
And in her hour
of greatest need,

43:30.058 --> 43:32.060
it's me that
she'll call for.

43:32.103 --> 43:34.366
And that infuriates Cip.

43:34.410 --> 43:36.891
He thinks, you know, you're
letting her get in trouble,

43:36.934 --> 43:38.806
you're letting her be in danger

43:38.849 --> 43:40.459
so that she will
need you.

43:40.503 --> 43:42.026
I find this scene
really interesting.

43:42.070 --> 43:45.813
It's two men talking about
what's best for a woman.

43:45.856 --> 43:47.292
Goodbye, Ciprien.

43:47.336 --> 43:48.859
♪

43:48.903 --> 43:50.992
[Crickets chirping]

43:52.123 --> 43:53.777
[Exhales sharply]

43:53.821 --> 43:55.300
[Gasps]

43:55.344 --> 43:59.870
♪

43:59.914 --> 44:01.306
[Inhales deeply]

44:01.350 --> 44:02.830
Spalding: When she finds out
she's pregnant,

44:02.873 --> 44:04.614
she calls Cip immediately.

44:04.658 --> 44:06.050
She knows this is Cip's baby.

44:06.094 --> 44:07.312
Ciprien:
Please leave a message.

44:07.356 --> 44:08.749
[Beep]Hey. Cip.

44:08.792 --> 44:10.707
I haven't heard from you.
Can you call me back

44:10.751 --> 44:12.361
when you get this?
It's important.

44:12.404 --> 44:13.971
Spalding: If you take
the position that

44:14.015 --> 44:16.365
everything happening
in the house was Lasher's doing,

44:16.408 --> 44:18.715
Rowan is getting pregnant
in that house

44:18.759 --> 44:20.761
because it was Lasher's will.

44:20.804 --> 44:22.501
Rowan: Are you there?

44:22.545 --> 44:24.068
♪

44:24.112 --> 44:25.940
Did you make this happen?

44:25.983 --> 44:29.378
So her next move is to try to
see if Tessa can talk to him

44:29.421 --> 44:30.684
and get an answer.

44:30.727 --> 44:31.728
♪

44:31.772 --> 44:33.121
Tessa's not
in her room.

44:33.164 --> 44:35.514
Didn't even sleep
in her bed.

44:35.558 --> 44:37.125
Are you worried?

44:37.168 --> 44:39.214
She'll answer
when she gets around to it.

44:39.257 --> 44:40.824
Maybe we should check in
with her friends.

44:40.868 --> 44:43.218
Who is this "we"?
There is no "we."

44:43.261 --> 44:44.654
She has a little instinct.

44:44.698 --> 44:46.351
"Is it strange
that Tessa's not here?

44:46.395 --> 44:48.179
Shouldn't we call
her friends?"

44:48.223 --> 44:52.183
She knows that Tessa was
on a crusade the day before

44:52.227 --> 44:55.012
about Deirdre's heart,
so she's worried about Tessa.

44:55.056 --> 44:57.145
She knows that Tessa
had that necklace

44:57.188 --> 44:59.713
and might be motivated
to do something foolish.

44:59.756 --> 45:00.975
[Indistinct conversation]Hey.

45:01.018 --> 45:02.454
What's going on?

45:02.498 --> 45:05.022
Jojo had a premonition
about Tessa.

45:05.066 --> 45:06.415
They start to put together

45:06.458 --> 45:08.373
exactly what could've happened
to Tessa.

45:08.417 --> 45:13.944
♪

45:13.988 --> 45:15.859
I really wanted
to pursue the idea

45:15.903 --> 45:19.167
of what would a witch hunter
look like in our world.

45:19.210 --> 45:23.301
Today we have a chance
to get real, solid proof

45:23.345 --> 45:24.781
of witchcraft.

45:24.825 --> 45:27.088
Spalding: They feel
that they aren't empowered,

45:27.131 --> 45:30.221
and so they're choosing
witches as the ones to blame.

45:30.265 --> 45:33.094
We will take this movement
to the next level.

45:33.137 --> 45:34.922
That is a Mayfair.

45:34.965 --> 45:37.402
That is a legacy witch
that our friend Keith here

45:37.446 --> 45:39.230
introduced us to.

45:39.274 --> 45:41.842
Spalding: These people
do feel disenfranchised,

45:41.885 --> 45:45.193
so they have a reason
to be angry at them,

45:45.236 --> 45:47.151
and now they've put
on top of that

45:47.195 --> 45:49.458
this whole notion
about witchcraft.

45:49.501 --> 45:56.073
♪

45:56.117 --> 45:57.858
[Groans]

45:57.901 --> 45:59.990
I think Rowan feels
very, very guilty

46:00.034 --> 46:01.513
about what's happened
to Tessa.

46:01.557 --> 46:03.820
Tessa came to her and said,
"Please use your power,"

46:03.864 --> 46:05.213
and Rowan walked away.

46:05.256 --> 46:06.780
I'm not getting anything.

46:06.823 --> 46:09.695
Rowan has learned that
she cares about this family

46:09.739 --> 46:11.523
and is connected
to this family.

46:11.567 --> 46:13.221
Use my blood.

46:13.264 --> 46:15.527
It's really the first
declaration like that

46:15.571 --> 46:17.573
in the show,
where she sees herself

46:17.616 --> 46:19.880
and declares herself
to be part of the family.

46:19.923 --> 46:21.403
Could that work?

46:21.446 --> 46:22.926
Let's find out.

46:22.970 --> 46:24.972
Tessa: Please! No!

46:25.015 --> 46:26.887
[Chuckles lightly]

46:26.930 --> 46:28.802
[Sobs]

46:28.845 --> 46:31.065
[Groaning]

46:31.108 --> 46:32.544
Lonnie?

46:32.588 --> 46:34.938
Spalding:
Rowan hears Tessa scream

46:34.982 --> 46:37.288
and knows she has to go in
without the family.

46:37.332 --> 46:41.466
♪

46:41.510 --> 46:43.860
[Groaning]

46:43.904 --> 46:46.210
They've all said, "Wait.
let's make this bloodless.

46:46.254 --> 46:47.472
Let's go together."

46:47.516 --> 46:49.344
She can't wait.
She has to go.

46:49.387 --> 46:50.867
She knows she has powers.

46:50.911 --> 46:52.303
She knows she can do
what she has to do.

46:52.347 --> 46:54.262
She's gonna kill them
if she needs to.

46:54.305 --> 46:56.873
She's got to save Tessa.
There's no question.

46:56.917 --> 46:59.223
[Gasping]
Take it. Please.

46:59.267 --> 47:00.834
Fucking witch!

47:00.877 --> 47:02.139
[Gunshot]

47:02.183 --> 47:04.185
♪

47:04.228 --> 47:08.798
And it's then that Rowan decides
she wants her full witchy power.

47:08.842 --> 47:10.191
[Gasping]

47:10.234 --> 47:12.323
Spalding: The moment
that Rowan calls to Lasher

47:12.367 --> 47:16.545
is a moment where she decides
that she wants vengeance.

47:16.588 --> 47:21.115
It's a moment of real fury
and destruction.

47:21.158 --> 47:24.683
She is going to pursue Keith
and use Lasher

47:24.727 --> 47:26.555
and she is gonna
bring him down.

47:26.598 --> 47:33.649
[Shouting in Latin]

47:33.692 --> 47:38.872
♪
